    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-12T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="449"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7515: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-12T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 12, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 12—11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>137. 1. The Government is reported to have issued late last night a mandate
                    making the following as members of the Hopei-Chahar Political Affairs
                    Commission: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Sung Cheh-yuan (Chairman); Wan Fu-lin; Wang I-tang; Liu Che; Li Ting-yu;
                            Chia Teh-yao; Hu Yu-kun; Kao Ling-wei; Wang <pb facs="0597" n="485"
                                xml:id="pg_485"/> Keh-min; Hsiao Chen-ying; Chin Teh-chun; Chang
                            Tze-chung; Cheng Ke; Chow Tso-min; Men Chih-chung; Shih Ching-ting; Leng
                            Chia-chi.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>2. The regulations governing the Commission are not yet known.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
